jteissler.csci1320.simplesql

Class AssignmentParser

  • java.lang.Object
    • jteissler.csci1320.simplesql.AssignmentParser
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Parser

    public class AssignmentParser
extends java.lang.Object
implements Parser
    Parses user input and determines what SQL command is being executed.
    The parse(String) method also acts as an error diagnosing method. If invalid syntax is entered into the parser, the parser will do its best to determine the specific cause of the issue and output information on the issue, as well as point it out in the logs with a "^" character pointing to the suspected issue.
    Author:
    J Teissler
    See Also:
    for documentation on overridden methods.

      • parse

        public void parse(java.lang.String input)
        Description copied from interface: Parser
        Parses out SQL commands, and sends the results to a database.
        Minimum Parsable Commands
        • CREATE DATABASE {database}
        • CREATE TABLE {database}.{table}
        • DROP DATABASE {database}
        • DROP TABLE {database}.{table}
        • INSERT "{value}" INTO {database}.{table}
        • UPDATE {database}.{table} SET COLUMN = {value1} WHERE COLUMN = {value2}
        • DELETE FROM {database}.{table}
        • DELETE FROM {database}.{table} WHERE COLUMN = {value}
        • SELECT * FROM {database}.{table}
        • SELECT * FROM {database}.{table} WHERE COLUMN = {value}
        Specified by:
        parse in interface Parser
        Parameters:
        input - The user input string.
